he roadmap of things to come the relationships that develop with students create unique recruiting opportunities browse our list of affiliate programs to find the right one for your company contact todd logan director of corporate relations for more information right rail successful partnerships great things happen when stanford engineers team up with supporters in industry stanley a completely autonomous volkswagen touareg won the 2005 darpa grand challenge a race around the nevada desert in which the cars had to make all their own driving decisions then in 2007 stanley's successor junior took second place in a race through the traffic of human stunt drivers and other robots in each case the team was based in the stanford artificial intelligence lab but benefitted greatly from expertise and other support from volkswagen of america's electronics research lab mdv mohr davidow ventures intel red bull and others stay connected itunes icon google+ icon facebook icon twitter icon linkedin icon stanford university school of engineering 475 via ortega stanford california 94305 4121 650.725 1575 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved accreditation info terms of use copyright complaints contact us
